<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <p>When using Zend_Db_Adapter_Oracle with Zend_Db_Select the table name should come in uppercase when quoted.</p>

<p>eg.</p>

<pre class="literal">
$db = new Zend_Db_Adapter_Oracle();
$select = new Zend_Db_Select($db);
$select-&gt;from('table');
</pre>

<p>should turn out to be</p>

<pre class="literal">
SELECT * FROM "TABLE"
</pre>

<p>but not</p>

<pre class="literal">
SELECT * FROM "table"
</pre>

<p>Because when quoting the table name in lowercase the database will retrun</p>

<pre class="literal">
ORA-00942: table or view does not exist
</pre>

